            "answer_text": "Type 27cc then press Alt+X. (If you\u2019re not familiar, that meant hold down the Alt key, then press and release the X key. Not necessary to press Shift.) When you release Alt+X, the 27cc will be replaced with \u27cc. Note this will also change the current font to Cambria Math. If you want it to be something else, don\u2019t forget to change it back. Note the string 27cc can also be 27CC. Both will result in the long division symbol. If you want the vinculum (the line at the top extending to the right) to extend over the dividend, the only way to do that is with an equation editor such as MathType. The built-in equation editor in Word won\u2019t do it. ",
